⚠️ Big heads up: Kobra X + OctoPrint
The Kobra X does NOT natively support OctoPrint, Klipper, Mainsail, or Fluidd. Most of the AI failure detection tools on GitHub are built around OctoPrint or Klipper, so this limits your options compared to a printer like the Kobra Max 3. The one monitoring platform confirmed compatible with the Kobra X is SimplyPrint. This doesn't kill your plan — it just shapes which tools you reach for first.

🥇 The best GitHub repos for your mission
Here's every relevant open-source project, ranked by how useful it is for your Kobra X setup:

1. 🔥 PrintGuard — 
oliverbravery/PrintGuard
This is the one, bro. It's the most complete, most modern, and most perfectly matched to your stack.

Key facts:

Single Docker container — runs on a Raspberry Pi 4/5 or any AMD64/ARM64 machine

No cloud, no subscription, no account — frames never leave your hardware

Detects: spaghetti, detachments, blobs, warping — scores every camera frame in real time

Auto-pauses or cancels print when a sustained defect is detected

Sends alerts via Telegram, Discord, or ntfy push to your phone

Works with OctoPrint, Klipper (Moonraker), and Bambu Lab — and via a REST API/MCP protocol, so you can connect other printers too

Home Assistant integration via MQTT — plays nicely with automations

MCP server built in — meaning you can point Claude or an IDE at it and automate everything

Try it in your browser right now with zero install: oliverbravery.github.io/PrintGuard

Install command (single line on Pi/Linux):

bash
docker run -d --name printguard --restart unless-stopped \
  -p 8000:8000 \
  -v printguard:/data \
  ghcr.io/oliverbravery/printguard
The AI model inside is a ShuffleNetV2 encoder trained specifically for FDM fault detection — it's fast, lightweight, and runs fully on-device .

2. 🕵️ Obico (formerly The Spaghetti Detective) — 
TheSpaghettiDetective/obico-server
The most widely used AI print monitoring platform in 2026. Supports OctoPrint and Klipper natively, self-hosted via Docker. Since Kobra X doesn't do OctoPrint natively, this is harder to hook up — but if you ever flash Klipper on the Kobra X (some Anycubic owners have done this on other Kobra variants ), Obico becomes an option. The mobile app is polished and free for basic use.

3. ⚡ klipper-print-failure-detection — 
CookiezRGood/klipper-print-failure-detection
A newer local AI failure detector specifically for Klipper . Uses a TensorFlow Lite model to detect spaghetti, blobs, cracks, and warping. Runs fully locally — no cloud. 23 stars on GitHub, updated June 2026 . Only relevant if you move to Klipper firmware.

4. 👀 OctoPrint-PiNozCam — 
DrAlexLiu/OctoPrint-PiNozCam
AI-powered camera monitoring on a Raspberry Pi for OctoPrint — also sends failure alerts via Telegram and Discord, free, no subscription. Not useful for stock Kobra X but worth knowing for future builds.

5. 🔬 PrintWatch — 
OctoPrint Plugin
Uses ML to detect failures, works with all filaments, colours, and printer types. Again, OctoPrint-dependent — worth flagging for if/when you expand the printer fleet.

6. 🛡️ 3D Print Sentinel — oliverbravery/3D-Print-Sentinel
Earlier project from the same dev as PrintGuard — runs the same Obico ML model locally on device. PrintGuard supersedes this, but it's useful reference code.

7. 🔎 Failure Detection Computer Vision — 
alexgrigoras/failure_detection_for_3d_printing
Research-level project using image matching (comparing slicer preview vs real print), object tracking, and spaghetti detection. More academic but useful if you want to build your own model.

