🔧 Quick wins for the Kobra X today (before software)
Based on real Kobra X community reports:

Wash the build plate before every print — one owner reported 130 hours with zero issues after doing just this

Tighten the eccentric nuts — loose wheels = rattling = layer shifts

Check belt tension — should feel like a guitar string, not floppy

Clean and lube the linear rails with PTFE or light machine oil if they feel gritty

Use Anycubic's own slicer to start — known profiles for the Kobra X already baked in

Reduce acceleration to 1500–2000 and infill speed to 120–150 mm/s if you hear rattling during fast infill

