📋 Step 1 — Prep the Raspberry Pi
Flash Raspberry Pi OS Lite (64-bit) to your SD card using Raspberry Pi Imager. Enable SSH and WiFi in the imager settings before flashing so you can SSH in wirelessly from day one.

bash
# SSH into your Pi first time
ssh pi@raspberrypi.local

# Update everything
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install Docker + Docker Compose in one go
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com | sh
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
sudo apt install -y docker-compose-plugin
newgrp docker

# Verify Docker works
docker run hello-world
🐳 Step 2 — Install PrintGuard (Docker)
This is the AI failure detection engine — one file, one command :

bash
# Make a folder for PrintGuard
mkdir ~/printguard && cd ~/printguard

# Create docker-compose.yml
nano docker-compose.yml
Paste this exactly:

text
version: "3.8"

services:
  printguard:
    image: ghcr.io/oliverbravery/printguard:latest
    container_name: printguard
    restart: unless-stopped
    ports:
      - "8000:8000"     # Web dashboard
      - "8554:8554"     # RTSP camera push (optional)
      - "1935:1935"     # RTMP camera push (optional)
    volumes:
      - printguard_data:/data
    devices:
      - /dev/video0:/dev/video0   # USB webcam — check with: ls /dev/video*
    privileged: false

volumes:
  printguard_data:
Save with Ctrl+X → Y → Enter, then launch:

bash
docker compose up -d

# Check it's running
docker compose logs -f printguard
